    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-03-31T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-03-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="483"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d483">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.00/1616a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-31T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 31, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. Personal for the Ambassador. There is widespread interest in this country in
                    the treatment being accorded to former Chancellor Schuschnigg. We realize that
                    any intercession on our part in favor of a non-American would probably be
                    resented by the German Government as an interference in their domestic affairs
                    and might accordingly have the opposite effect from that desired; nonetheless I
                    hope you will avail yourself of any available opportunity that may present
                    itself to point out in your personal capacity the widespread interest in this
                    case and the favorable effect on public opinion should he be permitted to leave
                    the country. This whole matter is naturally left to your entire discretion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
